====================================================================
1. ACCOUNT MANAGEMENT
====================================================================

CHANGING STORE OWNER
To transfer store ownership:
1. Go to Settings > Account
2. Click "Change store owner"
3. Enter new owner's email
4. New owner must accept within 7 days
5. All permissions transfer automatically

ADDING STAFF MEMBERS
You can add staff with different permission levels:
- Full access: Can access everything
- Limited access: Restricted to specific areas
- View only: Can view but not edit

To add staff:
1. Go to Settings > Account > Staff
2. Click "Add staff member"
3. Enter email and set permissions
4. Staff member receives invitation email

====================================================================
2. STORE CONFIGURATION
====================================================================

CUSTOMIZING YOUR THEME
To customize your store's appearance:
1. Go to Online Store > Themes
2. Click "Customize" on your active theme
3. Use the theme editor to modify:
   - Colors and fonts
   - Layout and sections
   - Navigation menus
   - Product pages
4. Preview changes before publishing

ADDING A CUSTOM DOMAIN
To use your own domain:
1. Go to Settings > Domains
2. Click "Add new domain"
3. Enter your domain name
4. Follow the DNS setup instructions
5. SSL certificate is automatically configured

====================================================================
3. PAYMENT PROCESSING
====================================================================

SUPPORTED PAYMENT GATEWAYS
Shopify supports:
- Shopify Payments (Stripe)
- PayPal
- Square
- Authorize.net
- And 100+ other gateways

SETTING UP SHOPIFY PAYMENTS
1. Go to Settings > Payments
2. Complete business information
3. Verify your identity
4. Set up payout destination
5. Payments are settled within 2-3 business days

TRANSACTION FEES
- Shopify Payments: No transaction fee
- Third-party gateways: 0.5%-2% fee based on plan
- No fee on Shopify Advanced plan

====================================================================
4. SHIPPING SETTINGS
====================================================================

CREATING SHIPPING ZONES
1. Go to Settings > Shipping
2. Click "Add shipping zone"
3. Select countries for the zone
4. Set rates based on:
   - Weight
   - Price
   - Flat rate
   - Free shipping over certain amount

SHIPPING CARRIERS INTEGRATION
Integrated carriers include:
- USPS
- UPS
- DHL Express
- Canada Post
- Sendle

Rates are calculated automatically at checkout.

====================================================================
5. PRODUCT MANAGEMENT
====================================================================

ADDING PRODUCTS
To add a new product:
1. Go to Products > Add product
2. Enter product details:
   - Title and description
   - Images and videos
   - Price and compare-at price
   - SKU and barcode
   - Inventory tracking
   - Shipping options
3. Organize into collections
4. Set SEO properties

INVENTORY MANAGEMENT
Shopify tracks inventory when:
- Products are sold
- Orders are fulfilled
- Returns are processed
- Manual adjustments are made

Low stock alerts can be configured in Settings > Inventory.

====================================================================
6. ORDER FULFILLMENT
====================================================================

FULFILLMENT OPTIONS
- Fulfill manually: Mark as fulfilled when shipped
- Bulk fulfillment: Fulfill multiple orders at once
- Automatic fulfillment: For digital products
- Third-party fulfillment: Connect to fulfillment service

PRINTING SHIPPING LABELS
1. Go to Orders page
2. Select orders to fulfill
3. Click "Create shipping label"
4. Select carrier and service
5. Buy and print label

====================================================================
7. CUSTOMER SUPPORT TOOLS
====================================================================

RESPONDING TO CUSTOMER INQUIRIES
All customer messages appear in:
- Inbox > Customers section
- Notifications menu

Best practices:
- Respond within 24 hours
- Use saved replies for common questions
- Set up automatic responses

HANDLING REFUND REQUESTS
1. Go to Orders > Select order
2. Click "Refund"
3. Select items to refund
4. Choose refund amount
5. Send refund confirmation to customer
